13. Write a PROLOG program to implement maxlist(L, M) so that M is the maximum
number in the list.

% Base case: maximum of a single-element list is the element itself
maxlist([M], M).

% Recursive case: compare head with max of tail
maxlist([H|T], M) :-
    maxlist(T, M1),
    (H > M1 -> M = H ; M = M1).

Sample
?- maxlist([3, 5, 2, 8, 4], M).
M = 8.
